******
[1] ECDC update
Date: Mon 11 Jul 2011
Source: European Centre for Disease Control (ECDC) [edited]
http://www.ecdc.europa.eu/en/activities/sciadvice/Lists/ECDC%20Reviews/ECDC_DispForm.aspx?List=512ff74f%2D77d4%2D4ad8%2Db6d6%2Dbf0f23083f30&ID=1146&RootFolder=%2Fen%2Factivities%2Fsciadvice%2FLists%2FECDC%20Reviews


Update since 11 Jul 2011
------------------------
As of today 11 Jul 2011, using the new case definition, the
cumulative number of non-HUS [hemolytic uremic syndrome] STEC [Shiga
toxin producing _Escherichia coli_] cases in the EU is 3041, including
16 deaths, and 757 HUS STEC cases, including 28 deaths.

In Germany, since 8 Jul 2011, 5 HUS STEC cases and 13 non-HUS STEC
cases have been newly reported. 4 HUS STEC cases and 12 non-HUS STEC
cases fell ill within the last 10 days (29 Jun-8 Jul 2011). The last
known date of illness onset in a patient with confirmed STEC O104 was
27 Jun 2011. The last reported date of illness onset among all cases
was 4 Jul 2011.

The United Kingdom reports an additional confirmed non-HUS STEC case,
in a visiting German national coming from Hamburg.

With regards to the outbreak in Bordeaux, France, since the last
update on 30 Jun 2011, 2 HUS STEC cases and 3 non-HUS STEC cases have
been newly confirmed. 3 of these cases had eaten sprouted seeds at an
event in Begles, and the other 2 (one HUS STEC, one non-HUS STEC) have
been attributed to person-to-person transmission.

Suspected cases (Germany: 156 HUS (7 deaths), France: 5 non-HUS STEC)
are not included.

--
